Carlo Ancelotti would prefer a move to Arsenal over Everton, the UK Mail reports. Ancelotti would favour the Gunners, because of the profile of the club and the fact he still has a house in London, from his time as Chelsea manager The Italian was sacked as Napoli manager on Tuesday, following a 4-0 win over Genk in the Champions League. However, it is understood that both Arsenal and Everton could pay a hefty compensation fee to land Ancelotti. There are discussions ongoing in Italy, as to whether Ancelotti has been sacked or placed on gardening leave. The specific terms of 60-year-old’s departure were still being finalised during discussions on Wednesday. Ancelotti has been replaced as Napoli manager by Gennaro Gattuso. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.